metadata.description: Inspired by nail and thread art, I explored the possibilities in generated art. Instead of perfectly symmetrical patterns I was attracted to the imperfect ones. It resulted in endless interesting patterns and shapes, this is a light and second version of Imperfect.

metadata.name: Colored Elementary Cellular Automaton #8
metadata.description:
The algorithm is based on Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton. 
This is a 1D cellular automaton with a neighborhood of 5 cells. This gives us 2^5 = 32 patterns for a neighborhood and 2^32 = 4.29B possible combinations!!! The size of the cell varies in a range of 2 to 8. There is a 15% of getting a black and white art.

Pattern rarity:
- Pattern 1 _25%
- Pattern 2 _30%
- Pattern 3 _35%
- Pattern 4 _15%

Note: The art might look in different resolutions because of the responsive view, but the color, pattern, and layout remain the same.

metadata.name: NEBULAE #95
metadata.description:
NEBULAE invites you to deep space exploration to search for rare nebulas. As a space explorer you will most likely encounter an NGC, the common nebula type, but on your travels there is an possibility you will witness the powerful creative forces of the universe.. or discover something even more magical.

This project was created with randomly generated Embergen particle simulations combined with cables.gl background setup. I want to deeply thank Murat Atimtay for all the help with this first generative mint and VerticalCryptoArt & somaticbits for their helpful resources.


[e] save as png

I hope this series sparks your imagination and love for color as it did for me.

- Walt

metadata.name: Conspiracy Theory #34
metadata.description:
The idea is inspired by the conspiracy board.

Conspiracy theories may go so far that even people, in newspapers and books, look for clues. 
The text is from Alice in Wonderland, which is randomly selected and then words are selected to be highlighted and circled, and eventually numbers may be written next to some of them to create a network of clues.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.
Made with P5js.

metadata.name: Abstract Calligraphy #77
metadata.description:
This work is inspired by Japanese avant-garde calligraphy (前衛書 Zenei-sho, or 墨象 Boku-shou). After World War II, the art of Japanese calligraphy was rapidly modernized. The ultimate result was avant-garde calligraphy that did not depict characters. They resembled the works of contemporary Western paintings of the same period, such as Abstract Expressionism and Art informel. In fact, some of the avant-garde calligraphy works were drawn with oil paint on canvas instead of Sumi ink on paper. So what is the difference between painting and calligraphy in those works?
A founder of avant-garde calligraphy said that the artistic essence of calligraphy art lies in the expression of a well-honed brushstroke, so the materials used are merely a medium. Then, is it possible for computer-drawn Bezier curves to become calligraphy art? This is an experiment in that.

This work is interactive. Clicking on the image or pressing the "m" key on the keyboard will randomly transform the shape of the strokes. There are 10 types of brushes. You can switch to other brushes by pressing the number keys on the keyboard (Touch devices switch with the direction of the swipe).
In addition, the strokes resize responsively to the window size, but the shape of the brush remains the same, so you can enjoy a different look by changing the screen's aspect ratio.

Dimensional Energies is an exploration of dimensions, connectedness and the energies within the different dimensions. The pieces are abstract expressions of how energies grow and change their shape, and how dimensions are gradually connected with each other.

metadata.name: Hypercolor Weavemaker #21
metadata.description:
Multiple weaves formulated by between 5 and 10 uniquely located walkers over 2000 frames.
Satisfying to watch the reveal. 
Rarity includes:
- Background color Black (approx 70%) - White (approx 20%) - Rare Palette Color (approx 70%) 
- One of thirty-one palettes
- Dominant Thrust - Horizontal (40%), Vertical (40%) or rare Equilibirum (20%) 
- Number of Walkers (5 to 10)
- Location of each Walker, defining the output shape

Made by P1xelboy :
@p1x3lboy June 2022

metadata.name: The Voyage #81
metadata.description:
The more we explore, the more things we realize there are to be explored. The more questions we find answers to, the more answers we find that require the right questions to be asked.

What is there beyond the edge of knowledge; what was, when things were none?

Will it be our body or our mind to discover that first?

And so The Voyage begins...

* * *

Press R to hide/show cosmic rain (takes a few seconds).
Press S to save as PNG.
